Overview
========

**hackerlates** makes backup copy of Hacker News submissions and comments::

   $ hackerlates --limit 3 jwilk
   https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=17907351
   2018-09-04 07:54:18
   > Both names are in use.
   >
   > From The Jargon File ([http://www.catb.org/jargon/html/H/Hanlons-Razor.html](http://www.catb.org/jargon/html/H/Hanlons-Razor.html)):
   >
   >  _At[http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html](http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html) it is claimed that Hanlon's Razor was coined by one Robert J. Hanlon of Scranton, PA. However, a curiously similar remark (“You have attributed conditions to villainy that simply result from stupidity.”) appears in Logic of Empire, a classic 1941 SF story by Robert A. Heinlein_ […] _._

